---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base
  title="Privacy — americawhat"
  description="What americawhat collects, why, and how it's handled."
  canonicalPath="/privacy/"
>
  <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; back to feed</a>
  <header class="page-head">
    <div class="page-eyebrow">Legal</div>
    <h1 class="page-title">Privacy</h1>
    <p class="page-updated">Last updated: 8 July 2026</p>
  </header>

  <article class="page-card page-prose">
    <p>Short version: we collect as little as possible, we don't sell it, and there are no ad trackers here.</p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Submissions & contact.</strong> If you use our form, we receive what you send — name, email, your message, and any optional link, city/state, or photo link. These are delivered to us by our form provider (Formspree).</li>
      <li><strong>Reactions.</strong> The WAT / LOL / SAME / DEAD buttons record anonymous, aggregate counts. They are not tied to your identity. Your own past votes may be remembered in your browser (local storage) so the buttons stay in sync on your device.</li>
      <li><strong>Server logs.</strong> Our host keeps standard technical logs (like IP address and browser type) for security and operations, as most web hosts do.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we use it</h2>
    <p>To review and respond to submissions, to run and protect the site, and to understand which posts land. That's it. We don't build advertising profiles.</p>

    <h2>Sharing</h2>
    <p>We don't sell your personal information. Limited processors help us operate — for example, Formspree handles form delivery and our web host serves the pages. They only receive what's needed to do that job.</p>

    <h2>Your choices</h2>
    <p>You can ask us to delete a submission you sent, or ask what we hold, by emailing <a href="mailto:hello@americawhat.com">hello@americawhat.com</a>. You can clear your browser's local storage anytime to reset your remembered reactions.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about privacy? <a href="mailto:hello@americawhat.com">hello@americawhat.com</a>.</p>
  </article>
</Base>
